WAS $38 MILLION HIGHER THAN IN 2005, PRIMARILY DUE TO THE ISSUANCE IN NOVEMBER 2005

OF $400 MILLION, 5.50% SENIOR NOTES DUE DECEMBER 1, 2015, AND THE ISSUANCE

