COMPANY WAS IN COMPLIANCE WITH THESE COVENANTS AND ALL OTHER COVENANTS RELATED

TO ITS RESPECTIVE DEBT INSTRUMENTS OUTSTANDING. PURSUANT TO THE TERMS OF THE

CREDIT AGREEMENT, THE COMPANY HAS AN OPTION TO INCREASE THE CREDIT AVAILABLE

UNDER THE FACILITY, NO MORE THAN ONCE A YEAR, UP TO A MAXIMUM FACILITY AMOUNT

OF $1.5 BILLION, SUBJECT TO THE SATISFACTION OF A RATINGS REQUIREMENT AND

CERTAIN OTHER CONDITIONS. THERE WAS NO AMOUNT OUTSTANDING UNDER THE CREDIT

AGREEMENT AS OF DECEMBER 31, 2006.

