RESERVES. AS AN INDICATOR OF THE CAUSAL EFFECT THAT A CHANGE IN ONE OR MORE

RISK FACTORS COULD HAVE ON RESERVES FOR HOMEOWNERS AND PERSONAL LINES OTHER, A

1% INCREASE (DECREASE) IN INCREMENTAL PAID LOSS DEVELOPMENT FOR EACH FUTURE

CALENDAR YEAR COULD RESULT IN A 1.1% INCREASE (DECREASE) IN LOSS RESERVES.

