THE MEANING OF

OTHER-THAN-TEMPORARY IMPAIRMENT AND ITS APPLICATION TO CERTAIN INVESTMENTS

IN NOVEMBER 2005, THE

FASB ISSUED FASB STAFF POSITION (FSP) FAS 115-1 AND FAS 124-1,

THE MEANING OF OTHER-THAN-TEMPORARY IMPAIRMENT AND ITS APPLICATION TO

CERTAIN INVESTMENTS.

THE FSP ADDRESSES THE DETERMINATION AS TO WHEN

AN INVESTMENT IS CONSIDERED IMPAIRED, WHETHER THAT IMPAIRMENT IS

OTHER-THAN-TEMPORARY, AND THE MEASUREMENT OF AN IMPAIRMENT LOSS. IT REQUIRES

THE ESTABLISHMENT OF A NEW COST BASIS SUBSEQUENT TO THE RECOGNITION OF AN

OTHER-THAN-TEMPORARY IMPAIRMENT AND CERTAIN DISCLOSURES ABOUT UNREALIZED LOSSES

THAT HAVE NOT BEEN RECOGNIZED AS OTHER-THAN-TEMPORARY IMPAIRMENTS. THE FSP IS

EFFECTIVE FOR REPORTING PERIODS BEGINNING AFTER DECEMBER 15, 2005. THE

COMPANY HAD PREVIOUSLY IMPLEMENTED THESE REQUIREMENTS. THEREFORE, THE ADOPTION

OF THE FSP HAD NO EFFECT ON THE COMPANYS RESULTS OF OPERATIONS, FINANCIAL

CONDITION OR LIQUIDITY.

