THE $1.75 BILLION DECLINE IN REINSURANCE RECOVERABLES

IN 2006 PRIMARILY REFLECTED SIGNIFICANT REINSURANCE RECOVERIES IN RELATED TO

PRIOR YEAR HURRICANE LOSSES, OPERATIONS IN RUNOFF (PRIMARILY GULF) AND VARIOUS

